                <div class="about-text">
                    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Bridging Philology & Technology</h2>
                    <p>
                        This program offers specialized training for philologists and researchers in modern digital methods for studying language evolution. It uniquely combines traditional linguistic analysis with cutting-edge computational tools, fully adopting the <strong>Open Access</strong> philosophy.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Target Audience:</strong> Open to philologists of all languages (Classics, Byzantine, Modern Greek, English, German, French, Spanish, Italian, etc.), educators, linguistics graduate students, digital humanities researchers, and language technology professionals.
                    </p>
                    <div style="background: #f0f4f8; padding: 2rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--primary); margin-top: 2rem; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;">
